## Content Authoring

Content lives in markdown files under `site/pages/`:

```markdown
---
type: Section
theme: light
---

# Welcome

Your content here.

[Call to Action](#)
```

**Page structure:**
- Create folder: `site/pages/about/`
- Add `page.yml` with title and metadata
- Add sections: `1-intro.md`, `2-team.md`, etc.

## Component Development

Components live in `foundation/src/components/`:

```jsx
// foundation/src/components/Hero/index.jsx
import { H1, P, cn } from '@uniweb/kit'

export function Hero({ content, params }) {
  const { title } = content.main?.header || {}
  const { theme = 'light' } = params

  return (
    <section className={cn('py-20', theme === 'dark' && 'bg-gray-900')}>
      <H1 text={title} />
    </section>
  )
}

export default Hero
```

Exposed components (selectable via `type:` in frontmatter) need a `meta.js` file.

